    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "I'd also omit the `--ws.addr` and `--http.addr` flags here and just have it listen on the local interface.  Because if you set the values to `0.0.0.0`, you are exposing the default-enabled rpc apis (`eth,net,web3`) outside of your local machine.  worst case scenario is that someone can DOS your node by repeatedly calling expensive RPC methods like `eth_estimateGas`.\r\n\r\nthis assumes that the external network interface on your machine is publicly reachable from the internet.",
